Represents a single facet field-value pair within a document.
<p>
Facet entries are typically included in {@link io.fluxzero.common.api.search.SerializedDocument} instances
to make the document searchable and filterable by discrete values. These entries are also used when computing
facet statistics and filtering using {@link io.fluxzero.common.api.search.constraints.FacetConstraint}.
<p>
The {@link #compareTo(FacetEntry)} implementation ensures consistent ordering of facet entries first by name,
then by value.

@see io.fluxzero.common.api.search.SerializedDocument
@see io.fluxzero.common.api.search.FacetStats
@see io.fluxzero.common.api.search.constraints.FacetConstraint
@see io.fluxzero.common.search.Facet

